 @Ammeo  As a Muslim, I’d like to clarify that Islam actually places a strong emphasis on compassion and kindness toward animals. The concept of halal slaughter, when practiced properly, is intended to minimize the suffering of the animal. The Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) taught us to treat animals with mercy and to ensure that the process is quick, with a sharp blade and without causing unnecessary pain.

Of course, like in any system, the ideals can sometimes be misapplied by people. If you saw or experienced cruelty done in the name of religion, that is deeply unfortunate—and I would agree that any cruelty is wrong, halal or not.

Your decision is personal and I respect that, but I hope people understand that Islam, in its teachings, calls for ethical treatment of all living beings—including animals.

